ooks at the reasons behind the publisher’s remarkable financial success, and he completes A World of Letters with a glimpse at the new initiatives that will propel the Press into a second exciting century.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aScholarly publishingxHistoryx20th centuryxConnecticutxNew HavenxConnecticutxNew Haven. 0aScholarly publishingzConnecticutzNew HavenxHistoryy20th century. 0aUniversity pressesxHistoryx20th centuryxConnecticutxNew Haven. 0aUniversity presseszConnecticutzNew HavenxHistoryy20th century. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030014272340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300142723423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300142723/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles